MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add foundational documentation for the Phase 2 sub-PMD superpage
(mTHP) correctness work atop PGCL.  Two files:

* sub-pmd-superpages.rst — architectural framing, PTE-walker contract,
  refcount accounting contract, lock discipline, and known race
  classes documented during Phase 1 forensic investigation of cow.c
  selftest failures on aarch64 PGCL=0/2 with transparent_hugepage=always.

* sub-pmd-superpages-walkers.rst — inventory of 30+ PTE-walking code
  paths classified by batch-awareness, lock state, rmap-modification
  scope, and risk for the orphan-PTE bug class.  Includes Phase 2c
  conversion priority and test vectors.

These documents are the basis for the upcoming RFC patch series.
The roadmap (Phase 2b through 2i) references them as the contract
of record for batch-aware mTHP handling.

No code changes.  Documentation only.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
